  <h3>Page background colour</h3>
  <p class="rich-text">We use <code>$color_nhsuk-grey-5</code> as a background tint. This is because:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>it reduces overall page glare</li>
    <li>the <a href="https://www.bdadyslexia.org.uk/employer/dyslexia-style-guide-2018-creating-dyslexia-friendly-content">British Dyslexia Association</a> recommends dark text on a light, but not white, background</li>
    <li>components with important information, like callouts, stand out</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="rich-text"><code>$color_nhsuk-white</code> is used to make important information stand out and for alternating backgrounds, for example on <a href="https://www.nhs.uk/">the NHS website home page</a>.</p>

